&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bank Registered Nurse - Post Acute Rehabilitation, Band 5&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary £24,907 - £ 30,165 + £3784 - £4592 HCAS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This is a bank role&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Are you interested in caring for patients who have recently had an acute hospital stay and need support to return to their own homes? Do you want to develop your assessment and nursing skills in a supportive but challenging environment? Perhaps you are someone who wants to move into Community nursing and wants to take the first step away from a hospital environment….if so then please consider coming and meeting the friendly team at Bromley Healthcare Rehabilitation Services, based at the Foxbury unit at Queen Marys hospital in Sidcup. We are a 30 bedded unit that provides rehabilitation to patients following a period of acute illness/injury.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The service also provides Intermediate Care Programmes to patients in Bromley and embraces nursing, therapy, social care, mental health and medical aspects of care. The truly multi disciplinary team assists with the rehabilitation of clients in a community based setting. Care is redirected to other generic services as required on discharge. Comprehensive assessments of complex cases are a key part of the service. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;As a Band 5 nurse you are responsible for ensuring the effective provision of nursing care for patients in the unit. You may be asked to act up for the senior Staff Nurse and will regularly take charge of a nursing caseload when you have achieved the relevant competencies.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You will share responsibility with the therapists for the management of rehabilitation programmes for patients while on the unit. You will carry continuing responsibility for the comprehensive assessment of care needs, the development, implementation and evaluation of care programmes. You are accountable for providing high standards of nursing care that embody the 6 C’s and for determining the activity of her/his support staff.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We are always looking for experienced nursing and therapy professionals to join our Bank of casual staff. We offer services in the following specialist areas community nursing, rehabilitation services and paediatrics throughout the borough of Bromley and beyond. Please see the jobs page on our website for further details.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
